<subSubSection pageId="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,493]" pageId="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species belongs to the recently defined genus 
<emphasis box="[887,1065,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="9">Teramoceroides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mantilleri" box="[1079,1278,151,176]" pageId="9" refString="Mantilleri, A. (2015 b) Nouveaux genres et especes de la tribu des Acratini (Coleoptera, Brentidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 120 (3), 267 - 296." type="journal article" year="2015" yearSuffix="b">Mantilleri, 2015b</bibRefCitation>
) as it presents the synapomorphies of the group: apical tooth of elytra with stiff setae below (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1105,187,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[349,1221,205,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[321,1266,193,1959]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Teramoceroides spathulifer Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♂ holotype. 19, Habitus; 20, apex of left elytron, dorsal view; 21, apex of left elytron, lateral view; 22, abdomen; 23, penis; 24, tegmen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246757/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), and sternite III of male with two paramedian projections (
<figureCitation box="[481,566,222,247]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[349,1221,205,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[321,1266,193,1959]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Teramoceroides spathulifer Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♂ holotype. 19, Habitus; 20, apex of left elytron, dorsal view; 21, apex of left elytron, lateral view; 22, abdomen; 23, penis; 24, tegmen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246757/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). In the case of 
<taxonomicName box="[749,899,222,247]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Teramoceroides" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="9" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="spathulifer" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[749,899,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="9">T. spathulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[908,998,222,247]" pageId="9" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[908,998,222,247]" pageId="9">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, these two paramedian projections are extremely reduced. In the key given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mantilleri" box="[606,819,257,282]" pageId="9" refString="Mantilleri, A. (2015 b) Nouveaux genres et especes de la tribu des Acratini (Coleoptera, Brentidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 120 (3), 267 - 296." type="journal article" year="2015" yearSuffix="b">Mantilleri (2015b)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species keys out with 
<taxonomicName authority="Boheman, 1833" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1833" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Teramoceroides" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="9" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1187,1302,257,282]" italics="true" pageId="9">T. gracilis</emphasis>
(Boheman, 1833)
</taxonomicName>
from South-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[448,519,292,317]" name="Brazil" pageId="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, because of reduced paramedian projections and lack of metallic sheen on elytra; both species also share dark membranous tergites of abdomen and first metatarsal segment dorso-ventrally flattened, without carina. They may be differentiated by the shape of the apical tooth of elytra (pointed in 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Teramoceroides" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="9" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9">T. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rounded in 
<taxonomicName box="[385,536,398,423]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Teramoceroides" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="9" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="spathulifer" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[385,536,398,423]" italics="true" pageId="9">T. spathulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[545,637,398,423]" pageId="9" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[545,637,398,423]" pageId="9">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
) and the general structure of the proximal sclerite of the endophallus (two paramedian rods linked in the middle by a pointed sclerite in 
<taxonomicName box="[911,1061,433,458]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Teramoceroides" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="9" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="spathulifer" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[911,1061,433,458]" italics="true" pageId="9">T. spathulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1069,1160,433,458]" pageId="9" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1069,1160,433,458]" pageId="9">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, without such rods in 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Teramoceroides" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="9" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9">T. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This endophallic sclerite is very similar to that of 
<emphasis box="[817,895,468,493]" italics="true" pageId="9">T. belti</emphasis>
(Sharp, 1895) from 
<collectingRegion box="[1124,1207,468,493]" country="Paraguay" name="Central" pageId="9">Central</collectingRegion>
America.
</paragraph>
